songs.title: Put The Radio On
songs.lyrics:
[Intro]
Put the radio on
Put the radio on (hello)
I don't wanna know I'm wrong
I don't wanna know I'm wrong

[Verse 1]
Sugar and spice, everything nice
Keep me on lock-down, put me on ice
'Cause I'm a really good girl, you a very bad guy
We're a little match made in Heaven if I say so, Yay-o
Come over here, boy, and play-o

[Pre-Chorus]
Work it out, work it right
Baby's lock 'n load tonight
Work it out, keep it tight
You're so rock and roll
Sold your soul now, baby

[Chorus]
Put the radio on
Put the radio on (yes, yes)
I don't wanna know I'm wrong
I don't wanna know I'm wrong
Put the radio on (and take a breath)
Put the radio on (come over here)
I don't wanna know I'm wrong
I don't wanna know I'm wrong for you

[Verse 2]
Peaches and cream, everyone's dream
You think you like me now? You should hear me sing
'Cause baby, I'm a fly girl and you're a big shot
If we got together, I know it would be hot-hot
Say so, stay-o, I'll give you somethin' to pray for

[Pre-Chorus]
Work it out, work it right
Baby's lock 'n load tonight
Work it out, keep it tight
You're so rock and roll
Sold your soul now, baby

[Chorus]
Put the radio on
Put the radio on (yes, yes)
I don't wanna know I'm wrong
I don't wanna know I'm wrong
Put the radio on (and take a breath)
Put the radio on (come over here)
I don't wanna know I'm wrong
I don't wanna know I'm wrong for you

[Verse 3]
I'm waiting by your back-door
Let me come in
I got your favorite dress on
Long hair, pinned up

[Bridge]
I like you lots, polka dots
Hope desire's in your thoughts
Thinking of you, dreaming of us
I like you lots, polka dots
Hope desire's in your thoughts
Thinking of you, dreaming of us

[Chorus]
Put the radio on
Put the radio on (yes, yes)
I don't wanna know I'm wrong
I don't wanna know I'm wrong
Put the radio on (and take a breath)
Put the radio on (come over here)
I don't wanna know I'm wrong
I don't wanna know I'm wrong for you

[Verse 4]
You know I got a taste for tonic and gin
You know I got an eye for fur and fine things
You know that I'm to die for, baby, give in
I told you when we met what you were in for

[Chorus]
Put the radio on
Put the radio on (yes, yes)
I don't wanna know I'm wrong
I don't wanna know I'm wrong
Put the radio on (and take a breath)
Put the radio on (come over here)
I don't wanna know I'm wrong
I don't wanna know I'm wrong for you
